al milieu at different times. He discusses Hooker's education, first pastoral experience, and career.Originally published in 1977.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aClergyxConnecticutxHartfordxBiography. 0aClergyzConnecticutzHartfordvBiography. 0aClergyzConnecticutzHartfordxBiography. 0aClergy. 0aCongregationalistsxConnecticutxHartfordxBiography. 0aCongregationalistszConnecticutzHartfordvBiography. 0aCongregationalistszConnecticutzHartfordxBiography. 0aCongregationalists. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  aA Model of Christian Charity.  aAnabaptists.  aAnne Bradstreet.  aAnne Hutchinson.  aAntinomian Controversy.  aAntinomianism.  aApprobation.  aBlasphemy.  aCalvinism.  aCatechism.  aChaplain.  aCharles Chauncy.  aChild of God.  aChristian Church.  aChurch covenant.  aChurch discipline.  aCommon grace.  aCongregational church.  aContrition.  aCotton Mather.  aCovenant theology.  aCreed.  aCurate.  aDamnation.  aDeacon.  aDisputation.  aDissenter.  aDivine call.  aDivine law.  aDoctrine of Election.  aDoctrine.  aEffectual calling.  aErudition.  aFall of man.  aGlorification.  aGod.  aHalf-Way Covenant.  aHead of the Church.  aHeresy.  aHeterodoxy.  aHigh church.  aHugh Peter.